{
  "stem": "2966.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of our people spoke already a little English because they were in England through the war, but I didn't.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, the first night I went to New York, took me a whole-- a whole night to get back to the ship because without speaking English, in the subways, everybody shows you different way.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But anyway, that's not important.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we sailed on that ship for quite a few months.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We went to Canada.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We went to Cuba.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We went to Nova Scotia, to Halifax, and Jamaica, where I contracted malaria, and I was in the hospital there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then I came back, I was in a hospital here, Marine hospital, Staten Island.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then came the day where I had to be repatriated to Poland, and I said, I'm not going.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As a seaman, you have permission to stay here 29 days, any nationality.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You get off the ship, you have official permission for 29 days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Anyway I started-- I took a test from the Coast Guard, and I got a Coast Guard card, permission to work on American ships.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then I had to go through the American unions because that's the only way you could get on a ship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Well anyway, I got on a ship, and we sailed, went to Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In Germany I got off the ship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I got a permission-- three day pass, and I went-- near Munich was a camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In the meantime, I found out some of my family survived, and they were in a DP camp in Foehrenwald.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I got a pass for three days, and I surprised them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They didn't know anything about-- they knew already I was alive, but they had no idea I was coming, and I came from America.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was a big deal.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
